canonical:
  title: 竹山大平院石佛
  author: 兪好仁
  language: lzh
  text: 征驢撫古抱酸辛一佛功成萬姓嗔人國已亡渠獨在長年風雨院邊身
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 竹山大平院石佛
  author: 兪好仁
  language: lzh
  text: 征驢撫古抱酸辛。一佛功成萬姓嗔。人國已亡渠獨在。長年風雨院邊身。
korean:
  title: 죽산 대평원 석불
  author: 유호인
  language: kor
  text: |-
    나귀 등에 옛일 생각 슬픔이 절로 날 제
    한 부처는 성공해도 뭇 백성은 말썽 많아
    남의 나라 망쳐 두고 저 홀로 남아 있어
    오랫동안 비바람이 그 몸에 뿌리더라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0060&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Stone Buddha at Taepyeong Temple, Juksan
  author: Yu Ho-in
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Upon a weary donkey I recall the ancient past,
    my heart heavy with sorrow.
    One Buddha stands complete while the common people remain aggrieved.
    The kingdom has fallen to ruin, yet this stone form endures alone,
    battered through long years by wind and rain at the temple's edge.
  footnotes:
    - Juksan refers to a region in present-day South Korea. Taepyeong Temple is a historical site where this stone Buddha statue stands as a remnant of a bygone era.
    - The poem reflects on the contrast between the eternal stone Buddha and the transience of human kingdoms and their subjects.
